44Ac 4:21 So the Council warned them even more strongly and then set them free. They saw that it was impossible to punish them, because the people were all praising God for what had happened. 
44Ac 4:22 The man on whom this miracle of healing had been performed was over forty years old. 
44Ac 4:23 As soon as Peter and John were set free, they returned to their group and told them what the chief priests and the elders had said. 
44Ac 4:24 When the believers heard it, they all joined together in prayer to God£º "Master and Creator of heaven, earth, and sea, and all that is in them! 
44Ac 4:25 By means of the Holy Spirit you spoke through our ancestor David, your servant, when he said, 'Why were the Gentiles furious; why did people make their useless plots? 
44Ac 4:26 The kings of the earth prepared themselves, and the rulers met together against the Lord and his Messiah.' 
44Ac 4:27 For indeed Herod and Pontius Pilate met together in this city with the Gentiles and the people of Israel against Jesus, your holy Servant, whom you made Messiah. 
44Ac 4:28 They gathered to do everything that you by your power and will had already decided would happen. 
