44Ac 5:17 Then the High Priest and all his companions, members of the local party of the Sadducees, became extremely jealous of the apostles; so they decided to take action. 
44Ac 5:18 They arrested the apostles and put them in the public jail. 
44Ac 5:19 But that night an angel of the Lord opened the prison gates, led the apostles out, and said to them, 
44Ac 5:20 "Go and stand in the Temple, and tell the people all about this new life." 
44Ac 5:21 The apostles obeyed, and at dawn they entered the Temple and started teaching. The High Priest and his companions called together all the Jewish elders for a full meeting of the Council; then they sent orders to the prison to have the apostles brought before them. 
44Ac 5:22 But when the officials arrived, they did not find the apostles in prison, so they returned to the Council and reported, 
