44Ac 5:40 They called the apostles in, had them whipped, and ordered them never again to speak in the name of Jesus; and then they set them free. 
44Ac 5:41 As the apostles left the Council, they were happy, because God had considered them worthy to suffer disgrace for the sake of Jesus. 
44Ac 5:42 And every day in the Temple and in people's homes they continued to teach and preach the Good News about Jesus the Messiah. 
44Ac 6:1 Some time later, as the number of disciples kept growing, there was a quarrel between the Greek-speaking Jews and the native Jews. The Greek-speaking Jews claimed that their widows were being neglected in the daily distribution of funds. 
