472Co 11:10 By Christ's truth in me, I promise that this boast of mine will not be silenced anywhere in all of Achaia. 
472Co 11:11 Do I say this because I don't love you? God knows I love you! 
472Co 11:12 I will go on doing what I am doing now, in order to keep those other "apostles" from having any reason for boasting and saying that they work in the same way that we do. 
472Co 11:13 Those men are not true apostles - they are false apostles, who lie about their work and disguise themselves to look like real apostles of Christ. 
