472Co 11:16 I repeat£º no one should think that I am a fool. But if you do, at least accept me as a fool, just so I will have a little to boast of. 
472Co 11:17 Of course what I am saying now is not what the Lord would have me say; in this matter of boasting I am really talking like a fool. 
472Co 11:18 But since there are so many who boast for merely human reasons, I will do the same. 
472Co 11:19 You yourselves are so wise, and so you gladly tolerate fools! 
472Co 11:20 You tolerate anyone who orders you around or takes advantage of you or traps you or looks down on you or slaps you in the face. 
472Co 11:21 I am ashamed to admit that we were too timid to do those things! But if anyone dares to boast about something - I am talking like a fool - I will be just as daring. 
472Co 11:22 Are they Hebrews? So am I. Are they Israelites? So am I. Are they Abraham's descendants? So am I. 
472Co 11:23 Are they Christ's servants? I sound like a madman - but I am a better servant than they are! I have worked much harder, I have been in prison more times, I have been whipped much more, and I have been near death more often. 
472Co 11:24 Five times I was given the thirty-nine lashes by the Jews; 
472Co 11:25 three times I was whipped by the Romans; and once I was stoned. I have been in three shipwrecks, and once I spent twenty-four hours in the water. 
472Co 11:26 In my many travels I have been in danger from floods and from robbers, in danger from my own people and from Gentiles; there have been dangers in the cities, dangers in the wilds, dangers on the high seas, and dangers from false friends. 
472Co 11:27 There has been work and toil; often I have gone without sleep; I have been hungry and thirsty; I have often been without enough food, shelter, or clothing. 
472Co 11:28 And not to mention other things, every day I am under the pressure of my concern for all the churches. 
472Co 11:29 When someone is weak, then I feel weak too; when someone is led into sin, I am filled with distress. 
472Co 11:30 If I must boast, I will boast about things that show how weak I am. 
472Co 11:31 The God and Father of the Lord Jesus - blessed be his name forever! - knows that I am not lying. 
472Co 11:32 When I was in Damascus, the governor under King Aretas placed guards at the city gates to arrest me. 
472Co 11:33 But I was let down in a basket through an opening in the wall and escaped from him. 
472Co 12:1 I have to boast, even though it doesn't do any good. But I will now talk about visions and revelations given me by the Lord. 
472Co 12:2 I know a certain Christian man who fourteen years ago was snatched up to the highest heaven (I do not know whether this actually happened or whether he had a vision - only God knows). 
472Co 12:3 I repeat, I know that this man was snatched to Paradise (again, I do not know whether this actually happened or whether it was a vision - only God knows), 
472Co 12:4 and there he heard things which cannot be put into words, things that human lips may not speak. 
472Co 12:5 So I will boast about this man - but I will not boast about myself, except the things that show how weak I am. 
472Co 12:6 If I wanted to boast, I would not be a fool, because I would be telling the truth. But I will not boast, because I do not want any of you to have a higher opinion of me than you have as a result of what you have seen me do and heard me say. 
