49Eph 3:11 God did this according to his eternal purpose, which he achieved through Christ Jesus our Lord. 
49Eph 3:12 In union with Christ and through our faith in him we have the boldness to go into God's presence with all confidence. 
49Eph 3:13 I beg you, then, not to be discouraged because I am suffering for you; it is all for your benefit. 
49Eph 3:14 For this reason I fall on my knees before the Father, 
49Eph 3:15 from whom every family in heaven and on earth receives its true name. 
49Eph 3:16 I ask God from the wealth of his glory to give you power through his Spirit to be strong in your inner selves, 
49Eph 3:17 and I pray that Christ will make his home in your hearts through faith. I pray that you may have your roots and foundation in love, 
49Eph 3:18 so that you, together with all God's people, may have the power to understand how broad and long, how high and deep, is Christ's love. 
49Eph 3:19 Yes, may you come to know his love - although it can never be fully known - and so be completely filled with the very nature of God. 
49Eph 3:20 To him who by means of his power working in us is able to do so much more than we can ever ask for, or even think of£º 
49Eph 3:21 to God be the glory in the church and in Christ Jesus for all time, forever and ever! Amen. 
49Eph 4:1 I urge you, then - I who am a prisoner because I serve the Lord£º live a life that measures up to the standard God set when he called you. 
49Eph 4:2 Be always humble, gentle, and patient. Show your love by being tolerant with one another. 
49Eph 4:3 Do your best to preserve the unity which the Spirit gives by means of the peace that binds you together. 
49Eph 4:4 There is one body and one Spirit, just as there is one hope to which God has called you. 
49Eph 4:5 There is one Lord, one faith, one baptism; 
49Eph 4:6 there is one God and Father of all people, who is Lord of all, works through all, and is in all. 
49Eph 4:7 Each one of us has received a special gift in proportion to what Christ has given. 
49Eph 4:8 As the scripture says, "When he went up to the very heights, he took many captives with him; he gave gifts to people." 
