66Rv 17:17 For God has placed in their hearts the will to carry out his purpose by acting together and giving to the beast their power to rule until God's words come true. 
66Rv 17:18 "The woman you saw is the great city that rules over the kings of the earth." 
66Rv 18:1 After this I saw another angel coming down out of heaven. He had great authority, and his splendor brightened the whole earth. 
66Rv 18:2 He cried out in a loud voice£º "She has fallen! Great Babylon has fallen! She is now haunted by demons and unclean spirits; all kinds of filthy and hateful birds live in her. 
66Rv 18:3 For all the nations have drunk her wine - the strong wine of her immoral lust. The kings of the earth practiced sexual immorality with her, and the merchants of the world grew rich from her unrestrained lust." 
66Rv 18:4 Then I heard another voice from heaven, saying, "Come out, my people! Come out from her! You must not take part in her sins; you must not share in her punishment! 
66Rv 18:5 For her sins are piled up as high as heaven, and God remembers her wicked ways. 
66Rv 18:6 Treat her exactly as she has treated you; pay her back double for all she has done. Fill her cup with a drink twice as strong as the drink she prepared for you. 
66Rv 18:7 Give her as much suffering and grief as the glory and luxury she gave herself. For she keeps telling herself£º 'Here I sit, a queen! I am no widow, I will never know grief !' 
66Rv 18:8 Because of this, in one day she will be struck with plagues - disease, grief, and famine. And she will be burned with fire, because the Lord God, who judges her, is mighty." 
66Rv 18:9 The kings of the earth who took part in her immorality and lust will cry and weep over the city when they see the smoke from the flames that consume her. 
66Rv 18:10 They stand a long way off, because they are afraid of sharing in her suffering. They say, "How terrible! How awful! This great and mighty city Babylon! In just one hour you have been punished!" 
66Rv 18:11 The merchants of the earth also cry and mourn for her, because no one buys their goods any longer; 
66Rv 18:12 no one buys their gold, silver, precious stones, and pearls; their goods of linen, purple cloth, silk, and scarlet cloth; all kinds of rare woods and all kinds of objects made of ivory and of expensive wood, of bronze, iron, and marble; 
66Rv 18:13 and cinnamon, spice, incense, myrrh, and frankincense; wine and oil, flour and wheat, cattle and sheep, horses and carriages, slaves, and even human lives. 
66Rv 18:14 The merchants say to her, "All the good things you longed to own have disappeared, and all your wealth and glamor are gone, and you will never find them again!" 
66Rv 18:15 The merchants, who became rich from doing business in that city, will stand a long way off, because they are afraid of sharing in her suffering. They will cry and mourn, 
66Rv 18:16 and say, "How terrible! How awful for the great city! She used to dress herself in linen, purple, and scarlet, and cover herself with gold ornaments, precious stones, and pearls! 
66Rv 18:17 And in one hour she has lost all this wealth!" All the ships' captains and passengers, the sailors and all others who earn their living on the sea, stood a long way off, 
66Rv 18:18 and cried out as they saw the smoke from the flames that consumed her£º "There never has been another city like this great city!" 
66Rv 18:19 They threw dust on their heads, they cried and mourned, saying, "How terrible! How awful for the great city! She is the city where all who have ships sailing the seas became rich on her wealth! And in one hour she has lost everything!" 
66Rv 18:20 Be glad, heaven, because of her destruction! Be glad, God's people and the apostles and prophets! For God has condemned her for what she did to you! 
66Rv 18:21 Then a mighty angel picked up a stone the size of a large millstone and threw it into the sea, saying, "This is how the great city Babylon will be violently thrown down and will never be seen again. 
66Rv 18:22 The music of harps and of human voices, of players of the flute and the trumpet, will never be heard in you again! No workman in any trade will ever be found in you again; and the sound of the millstone will be heard no more! 
66Rv 18:23 Never again will the light of a lamp be seen in you; no more will the voices of brides and grooms be heard in you. Your merchants were the most powerful in all the world, and with your false magic you deceived all the peoples of the world!" 
66Rv 18:24 Babylon was punished because the blood of prophets and of God's people was found in the city; yes, the blood of all those who have been killed on earth. 
66Rv 19:1 After this I heard what sounded like the roar of a large crowd of people in heaven, saying, "Praise God! Salvation, glory, and power belong to our God! 
66Rv 19:2 True and just are his judgments! He has condemned the prostitute who was corrupting the earth with her immorality. God has punished her because she killed his servants." 
66Rv 19:3 Again they shouted, "Praise God! The smoke from the flames that consume the great city goes up forever and ever!" 
66Rv 19:4 The twenty-four elders and the four living creatures fell down and worshiped God, who was seated on the throne. They said, "Amen! Praise God!" 
66Rv 19:5 Then there came from the throne the sound of a voice, saying, "Praise our God, all his servants and all people, both great and small, who have reverence for him!" 
66Rv 19:6 Then I heard what sounded like a crowd, like the sound of a roaring waterfall, like loud peals of thunder. I heard them say, "Praise God! For the Lord, our Almighty God, is King! 
66Rv 19:7 Let us rejoice and be glad; let us praise his greatness! For the time has come for the wedding of the Lamb, and his bride has prepared herself for it. 
66Rv 19:8 She has been given clean shining linen to wear." (The linen is the good deeds of God's people.) 
66Rv 19:9 Then the angel said to me, "Write this£º Happy are those who have been invited to the wedding feast of the Lamb." And the angel added, "These are the true words of God." 
66Rv 19:10 I fell down at his feet to worship him, but he said to me, "Don't do it! I am a servant together with you and with other believers, all those who hold to the truth that Jesus revealed. Worship God!" For the truth that Jesus revealed is what inspires the prophets. 
66Rv 19:11 Then I saw heaven open, and there was a white horse. Its rider is called Faithful and True; it is with justice that he judges and fights his battles. 
66Rv 19:12 His eyes were like a flame of fire, and he wore many crowns on his head. He had a name written on him, but no one except himself knows what it is. 
66Rv 19:13 The robe he wore was covered with blood. His name is "The Word of God." 
66Rv 19:14 The armies of heaven followed him, riding on white horses and dressed in clean white linen. 
66Rv 19:15 Out of his mouth came a sharp sword, with which he will defeat the nations. He will rule over them with a rod of iron, and he will trample out the wine in the wine press of the furious anger of the Almighty God. 
66Rv 19:16 On his robe and on his thigh was written the name£º "King of kings and Lord of lords." 
66Rv 19:17 Then I saw an angel standing on the sun. He shouted in a loud voice to all the birds flying in midair£º "Come and gather together for God's great feast! 
66Rv 19:18 Come and eat the flesh of kings, generals, and soldiers, the flesh of horses and their riders, the flesh of all people, slave and free, great and small!" 
66Rv 19:19 Then I saw the beast and the kings of the earth and their armies gathered to fight against the one who was riding the horse and against his army. 
66Rv 19:20 The beast was taken prisoner, together with the false prophet who had performed miracles in his presence. (It was by those miracles that he had deceived those who had the mark of the beast and those who had worshiped the image of the beast.) The beast and the false prophet were both thrown alive into the lake of fire that burns with sulfur. 
66Rv 19:21 Their armies were killed by the sword that comes out of the mouth of the one who was riding the horse; and all the birds ate all they could of their flesh. 
66Rv 20:1 Then I saw an angel coming down from heaven, holding in his hand the key of the abyss and a heavy chain. 
66Rv 20:2 He seized the dragon, that ancient serpent - that is, the Devil, or Satan - and chained him up for a thousand years. 
66Rv 20:3 The angel threw him into the abyss, locked it, and sealed it, so that he could not deceive the nations any more until the thousand years were over. After that he must be set loose for a little while. 
66Rv 20:4 Then I saw thrones, and those who sat on them were given the power to judge. I also saw the souls of those who had been executed because they had proclaimed the truth that Jesus revealed and the word of God. They had not worshiped the beast or its image, nor had they received the mark of the beast on their foreheads or their hands. They came to life and ruled as kings with Christ for a thousand years. 
66Rv 20:5 (The rest of the dead did not come to life until the thousand years were over.) This is the first raising of the dead. 
66Rv 20:6 Happy and greatly blessed are those who are included in this first raising of the dead. The second death has no power over them; they shall be priests of God and of Christ, and they will rule with him for a thousand years. 
66Rv 20:7 After the thousand years are over, Satan will be set loose from his prison, 
66Rv 20:8 and he will go out to deceive the nations scattered over the whole world, that is, Gog and Magog. Satan will bring them all together for battle, as many as the grains of sand on the seashore. 
66Rv 20:9 They spread out over the earth and surrounded the camp of God's people and the city that he loves. But fire came down from heaven and destroyed them. 
66Rv 20:10 Then the Devil, who deceived them, was thrown into the lake of fire and sulfur, where the beast and the false prophet had already been thrown; and they will be tormented day and night forever and ever. 
66Rv 20:11 Then I saw a great white throne and the one who sits on it. Earth and heaven fled from his presence and were seen no more. 
66Rv 20:12 And I saw the dead, great and small alike, standing before the throne. Books were opened, and then another book was opened, the book of the living. The dead were judged according to what they had done, as recorded in the books. 
66Rv 20:13 Then the sea gave up its dead. Death and the world of the dead also gave up the dead they held. And all were judged according to what they had done. 
66Rv 20:14 Then death and the world of the dead were thrown into the lake of fire. (This lake of fire is the second death.) 
66Rv 20:15 Those who did not have their name written in the book of the living were thrown into the lake of fire. 
66Rv 21:1 Then I saw a new heaven and a new earth. The first heaven and the first earth disappeared, and the sea vanished. 
66Rv 21:2 And I saw the Holy City, the new Jerusalem, coming down out of heaven from God, prepared and ready, like a bride dressed to meet her husband. 
66Rv 21:3 I heard a loud voice speaking from the throne£º "Now God's home is with people! He will live with them, and they shall be his people. God himself will be with them, and he will be their God. 
66Rv 21:4 He will wipe away all tears from their eyes. There will be no more death, no more grief or crying or pain. The old things have disappeared." 
66Rv 21:5 Then the one who sits on the throne said, "And now I make all things new!" He also said to me, "Write this, because these words are true and can be trusted." 
66Rv 21:6 And he said, "It is done! I am the first and the last, the beginning and the end. To anyone who is thirsty I will give the right to drink from the spring of the water of life without paying for it. 
66Rv 21:7 Those who win the victory will receive this from me£º I will be their God, and they will be my children. 
66Rv 21:8 But cowards, traitors, perverts, murderers, the immoral, those who practice magic, those who worship idols, and all liars - the place for them is the lake burning with fire and sulfur, which is the second death." 
66Rv 21:9 One of the seven angels who had the seven bowls full of the seven last plagues came to me and said, "Come, and I will show you the Bride, the wife of the Lamb." 
66Rv 21:10 The Spirit took control of me, and the angel carried me to the top of a very high mountain. He showed me Jerusalem, the Holy City, coming down out of heaven from God 
66Rv 21:11 and shining with the glory of God. The city shone like a precious stone, like a jasper, clear as crystal. 
66Rv 21:12 It had a great, high wall with twelve gates and with twelve angels in charge of the gates. On the gates were written the names of the twelve tribes of the people of Israel. 
66Rv 21:13 There were three gates on each side£º three on the east, three on the south, three on the north, and three on the west. 
66Rv 21:14 The city's wall was built on twelve foundation stones, on which were written the names of the twelve apostles of the Lamb. 
66Rv 21:15 The angel who spoke to me had a gold measuring stick to measure the city, its gates, and its wall. 
66Rv 21:16 The city was perfectly square, as wide as it was long. The angel measured the city with his measuring stick£º it was fifteen hundred miles long and was as wide and as high as it was long. 
66Rv 21:17 The angel also measured the wall, and it was 216 feet high, according to the standard unit of measure which he was using. 
66Rv 21:18 The wall was made of jasper, and the city itself was made of pure gold, as clear as glass. 
66Rv 21:19 The foundation stones of the city wall were adorned with all kinds of precious stones. The first foundation stone was jasper, the second sapphire, the third agate, the fourth emerald, 
66Rv 21:20 the fifth onyx, the sixth carnelian, the seventh yellow quartz, the eighth beryl, the ninth topaz, the tenth chalcedony, the eleventh turquoise, the twelfth amethyst. 
66Rv 21:21 The twelve gates were twelve pearls; each gate was made from a single pearl. The street of the city was of pure gold, transparent as glass. 
66Rv 21:22 I did not see a temple in the city, because its temple is the Lord God Almighty and the Lamb. 
66Rv 21:23 The city has no need of the sun or the moon to shine on it, because the glory of God shines on it, and the Lamb is its lamp. 
66Rv 21:24 The peoples of the world will walk by its light, and the kings of the earth will bring their wealth into it. 
66Rv 21:25 The gates of the city will stand open all day; they will never be closed, because there will be no night there. 
66Rv 21:26 The greatness and the wealth of the nations will be brought into the city. 
66Rv 21:27 But nothing that is impure will enter the city, nor anyone who does shameful things or tells lies. Only those whose names are written in the Lamb's book of the living will enter the city. 
66Rv 22:1 The angel also showed me the river of the water of life, sparkling like crystal, and coming from the throne of God and of the Lamb 
66Rv 22:2 and flowing down the middle of the city's street. On each side of the river was the tree of life, which bears fruit twelve times a year, once each month; and its leaves are for the healing of the nations. 
66Rv 22:3 Nothing that is under God's curse will be found in the city. The throne of God and of the Lamb will be in the city, and his servants will worship him. 
66Rv 22:4 They will see his face, and his name will be written on their foreheads. 
66Rv 22:5 There shall be no more night, and they will not need lamps or sunlight, because the Lord God will be their light, and they will rule as kings forever and ever. 
66Rv 22:6 Then the angel said to me, "These words are true and can be trusted. And the Lord God, who gives his Spirit to the prophets, has sent his angel to show his servants what must happen very soon." 
66Rv 22:7 "Listen!" says Jesus. "I am coming soon! Happy are those who obey the prophetic words in this book!" 
66Rv 22:8 I, John, have heard and seen all these things. And when I finished hearing and seeing them, I fell down at the feet of the angel who had shown me these things, and I was about to worship him. 
66Rv 22:9 But he said to me, "Don't do it! I am a servant together with you and with your brothers the prophets and of all those who obey the words in this book. Worship God!" 
66Rv 22:10 And he said to me, "Do not keep the prophetic words of this book a secret, because the time is near when all this will happen. 
66Rv 22:11 Whoever is evil must go on doing evil, and whoever is filthy must go on being filthy; whoever is good must go on doing good, and whoever is holy must go on being holy." 
66Rv 22:12 "Listen!" says Jesus. "I am coming soon! I will bring my rewards with me, to give to each one according to what he has done. 
66Rv 22:13 I am the first and the last, the beginning and the end." 
66Rv 22:14 Happy are those who wash their robes clean and so have the right to eat the fruit from the tree of life and to go through the gates into the city. 
66Rv 22:15 But outside the city are the perverts and those who practice magic, the immoral and the murderers, those who worship idols and those who are liars both in words and deeds. 
66Rv 22:16 "I, Jesus, have sent my angel to announce these things to you in the churches. I am descended from the family of David; I am the bright morning star." 
66Rv 22:17 The Spirit and the Bride say, "Come!" Everyone who hears this must also say, "Come!" Come, whoever is thirsty; accept the water of life as a gift, whoever wants it. 
66Rv 22:18 I, John, solemnly warn everyone who hears the prophetic words of this book£º if any add anything to them, God will add to their punishment the plagues described in this book. 
66Rv 22:19 And if any take anything away from the prophetic words of this book, God will take away from them their share of the fruit of the tree of life and of the Holy City, which are described in this book. 
66Rv 22:20 He who gives his testimony to all this says, "Yes indeed! I am coming soon!" So be it. Come, Lord Jesus! 
66Rv 22:21 May the grace of the Lord Jesus be with everyone. 
